  "prompt": "What is the difference between angular velocity and angular acceleration?",
  "response": "Angular velocity and angular acceleration are both concepts used to describe the rotational motion of an object, but they represent different physical quantities.\n\n### Angular Velocity (\u03c9)\n- **Definition**: Angular velocity is a measure of how quickly an object rotates around a specific axis. It quantifies the rate of change of the angular position of the object with respect to time.\n- **Units**: It is typically measured in radians per second (rad/s) or degrees per second (\u00b0/s).\n- **Direction**: Angular velocity is a vector quantity, meaning it has both magnitude and direction. The direction is usually determined by the right-hand rule, which defines the orientation of the rotation axis.\n- **Formula**: The average angular velocity can be calculated using:\n  \\[\n  \\omega = \\frac{\\Delta \\theta}{\\Delta t}\n  \\]\n  where \\( \\Delta \\theta \\) is the change in angular position and \\( \\Delta t \\) is the change in time. \n\n### Angular Acceleration (\u03b1)\n- **Definition**: Angular acceleration is a measure of how quickly the angular velocity of an object is changing over time. It quantifies the rate of change of angular velocity with respect to time.\n- **Units**: It is usually expressed in radians per second squared (rad/s\u00b2).\n- **Direction**: Like angular velocity, angular acceleration is also a vector quantity and has both magnitude and direction. A positive angular acceleration indicates an increase in angular speed, while a negative angular acceleration (or deceleration) indicates a decrease in angular speed.\n- **Formula**: The average angular acceleration can be defined as:\n  \\[\n  \\alpha = \\frac{\\Delta \\omega}{\\Delta t}\n  \\]\n  where \\( \\Delta \\omega \\) is the change in angular velocity and \\( \\Delta t \\) is the change in time.\n\n### Summary\n- **Angular velocity (\u03c9)** measures how fast something is rotating, while **angular acceleration (\u03b1)** measures how fast the rate of rotation is changing.\n- Angular velocity describes the rotation itself, and angular acceleration describes how that rotation is changing.",
